[stdout] {"type":"text","timestamp":1772768615173,"sessionID":"ses_33ec4c5acffeouDHK9VlMNOfNk","part":{"id":"prt_cc13e3f08001RHshoKjT0uOZwm","sessionID":"ses_33ec4c5acffeouDHK9VlMNOfNk","messageID":"msg_cc13e3bf20011eCCp4NgMbFIoS","type":"text","text":"Built a minimal RP2040 breakout in `index.circuit.tsx` with `routingDisabled` on the board, a USB-C connector, ESD protection, 3.3 V LDO, external QSPI flash, 12 MHz crystal, and a GPIO25 status LED. All major parts come from JLCPCB imports in `imports/RP2040.tsx`, `imports/TYPE_C_31_M_12.tsx`, `imports/ME6211C33M5G_N.tsx`, `imports/W25Q16JVUXIQ.tsx`, `imports/X322516MLB4SI.tsx`, `imports/USBLC6_2SC6.tsx`, and `imports/XL_1608SYGC_06.tsx`, with only generic passives defined directly in the board file.\n\n- The board is a compact `42mm x 24mm` breakout with USB data routed logically in the netlist, while autorouting stays disabled as requested.\n- The USB-C interface includes CC pull-downs, tied shield/ground pins, VBUS input, and a USBLC6 ESD array between the connector and the RP2040 USB pins.\n- Power uses a simple `ME6211C33M5G-N` LDO from VBUS to `V3_3`, plus local decoupling and the RP2040 internal regulator capacitor network.\n- Boot support uses imported `W25Q16JVUXIQ` flash on the RP2040 QSPI pins and an imported 12 MHz crystal with load capacitors.\n- The LED path is `GPIO25 -> 1k -> green LED -> GND`, matching the common Pico-style onboard indicator choice.\n- I ran `tsci build --site --use-cdn-javascript` successfully, which generated output in `dist/`, and `tsci snapshot`, which produced `__snapshots__/index.circuit-pcb.snap.svg` and `__snapshots__/index.circuit-schematic.snap.svg`.\n\nAssumptions used:\n- A minimal breakout means the core RP2040 support circuitry is included, while GPIOs are exposed as named nets rather than fully populated pin headers.\n- USB power is bus-powered only, with no battery or separate VIN path.\n- A compact USB-C receptacle from JLCPCB is acceptable in place of a bare footprint-only connector since registry components were excluded but JLC imports were allowed.","time":{"start":1772768615171,"end":1772768615171}}}

