[stdout] {"type":"text","timestamp":1772769558022,"sessionID":"ses_33eb7c3a6ffeskOY7ThYJO7DiE","part":{"id":"prt_cc14ca9e7001moZKGI3V7noInW","sessionID":"ses_33eb7c3a6ffeskOY7ThYJO7DiE","messageID":"msg_cc14ca67d0013LLC1y33NakEev","type":"text","text":"Built a minimal RP2040 breakout in `index.circuit.tsx` with a USB-C port, 3.3 V regulator, reset button, 12 MHz crystal, power decoupling, USB ESD protection, and a GPIO25 status LED. The board uses only locally imported JLCPCB components from `imports/` and sets `routingDisabled` on the root `<board />` so autorouting stays off.\n\n- The main design lives in `index.circuit.tsx` and places the RP2040, USB-C receptacle, regulator, crystal network, LED path, and mounting holes on a compact `42mm x 30mm` board.\n- Imported JLCPCB parts were generated into `imports/RP2040.tsx`, `imports/TYPE_C_16PIN_2MD_073_.tsx`, `imports/XC6206P332MR.tsx`, `imports/USBLC6_2SC6.tsx`, `imports/X322512MSB4SI.tsx`, `imports/XL_1608SYGC_06.tsx`, `imports/HX_3x4x2_2P_1_6N_TACTILE_SWITCH.tsx`, and the passive part wrappers in `imports/`.\n- I assumed a minimal USB-powered breakout rather than a fully bootable dev board, so the RP2040 core support, USB data path, RUN pull-up/reset switch, and LED are present while external QSPI flash and pin-header breakout rows are intentionally omitted.\n- I ran `tsci build --site --use-cdn-javascript`, which completed successfully and generated output in `dist/`.\n- I ran `tsci snapshot`, which produced snapshot artifacts in `__snapshots__/index.circuit-pcb.snap.svg` and `__snapshots__/index.circuit-schematic.snap.svg`.","time":{"start":1772769558021,"end":1772769558021}}}

